Jaylon Kerley has been charged after he was caught on camera spitting on pizza dough he was preparing at a concession stand in Comerica Park in Detroit in the US. WXYZÂ reports Kerley has been charged with one count of Food Law Violations, a 4-year felony, and a lesser charge which could lead to three months in jail. During a court appearance on Tuesday, he was given a $100,000/10 percent bond. FOX2 reports the judge ruled Kerley must also get medically tested, including a hepatitis panel, which is an array of tests used to detect hepatitis infections.